The paper discusses the use of deep learning for automated diagnosis of retinal OCT images, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence (AI) and medical imaging (MED) techniques, which makes cs.AI and cs.MED likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of information retrieval (IR) techniques for coping with differences in patient race, which makes cs.IR a possible sub-category.
